title: H.S. field hockey: NV/Old Tappan triumhps in penalty stroke shootout
text:
H.S. field hockey: NV/Old Tappan triumhps in penalty stroke shootout October 12, 2015 Last updated: Monday, October 12, 2015, 1:15 AM Herald News Print 
Maura Wiley had a goal in the second round of the penalty stroke shootout to hand fourth-seeded NV/Old Tappan a 5-4 victory over fifth-seeded Dwight-Englewood after a scoreless tie through regulation and two overtimes in a Bergen County tournament quarterfinal field hockey game in Old Tappan on Sunday. 
Wiley and Jillian Johnson each had two goals in the shootout and Carol Oberhelman had one for NV/Old Tappan and Sydney Zahn had two goals and Olivia Fuld and Katie Anderson one apiece for Dwight-Englewood in the penalty stroke portion of the game. Golden Knights goaltender Maya Vanderlinden made nine saves and Lady Bulldogs goaltender Emily Nebens had 19 saves. 
WESTWOOD 1, NV/DEMAREST 0 (at Washington Township): Samantha Hywell scored off an assist from Neeve Twomey in the second half to give the third-seeded Cardinals the win over the sixth-seeded Norsewomen. Delanie Glock made 11 saves for the shutout for Westwood and Prerna Khemlani had 11 saves for NV/Demarest. 
NORTHERN HIGHLANDS 4, RIVER DELL 0 (at Allendale): Gabby Pontone scored two goals and Jennifer Asnis had a goal and assist to lead the second-seeded Highlanders past the seventh-seeded Golden Hawks. Quinn Slayne made four saves for the Northern Highlands shutout. Â© 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
